Product name: 1996, Curly Beanie Baby, Ty Beanie Babies Rare, Curly Beanie Baby With Errors
Description:
1996 Curly Beanie Baby, Ty Beanie Babies Rare, Curly Beanie Baby With Errors
You are looking at a very rare version of the Curly Beanie Baby Bear. 
Curly the Bear is new and has never been played with.
He has been in a plastic ziploc bag in a container for the last 20 years.
Curly Bear's fur is the less common nappy texture, rather than plush.
There were only 1,000,000 Curly Beanie Babies made.
This Curly Beanie Baby With Errors was born April 12, 1996 and has the following errors:
 
1.    He has a brown nose.
​2.   His Ty Beanie Baby swing tag has the misspelling  "origiinal" versus "original"
      in the yellow star on the front of the Beanie Baby tag.
​3.  There is an extra space of the poem after the to, "To   this bear"
4.  On the back of the Beanie Baby swing tag "surface" was misspelled "suface", and a sticker was placed over the tag to correct 
     the spelling before it left the factory.
5.  Curly Bear doesn't have any stamp in his Tush Tag, which dates him prior to May of 1998 when the stamp was added to all of 
     the tush tags.
6.  Not that I'm sure if it matters, but his Tush Tag says 1993, and his birthday year is 1996 . 
     At least he was copyrighted before he was born.
 
​He is Handmade in China, and has PE Pellets.
This Curly Beanie Baby was purchased at a Candy Kitchen in Delaware at the beach.
The pictures are of the exact Curly Beanie Baby that you will receive.  They are taken with a high resolution camera.
The shipping is free and Curly Bear will be shipped USPS Express Mail.

Description:
VINTAGE KARU ARKE AURORA BOREALIS RHINESTONE BROOCH AND EARRINGS SET (Ref: 160327)
DESCRIPTION
This is a gorgeous brooch and earrings set from Karu Arké Inc (1954 – 1970s).
The stones are multi colored Aurora Borealis rhinestones with the most dominant color being blue stones with other colors appearing with light and movement. They are incredibly sparkly.
The brooch is an open circle constructed from 6 circles with the rhinestones in prong settings over an open metal work flower. Each flower has one central rhinestone and 6 rhinestones on the petals. 
The brooch closes with a rollover clasp.
The earrings are constructed from 3 of the same flower circles each. The circles are curved so that they hug the ear. There is a right earring and a left earring. 
The earrings are clip ons.
For comfort, the earrings will be provided with removable cushion covers on the clip on section.
The setting is a rich gold metal.
Each of the earrings is stamped with Karu Arké Inc.
MEASUREMENTS
The brooch is 1.75 inches / 45 mm across.
The earrings are a touch over 1.5 inches / 40 mm long.
Each of the flower circles is 0.75 of an inch / 20 mm across.
AGE
The brooch and earrings are circa 1950s / 1960s.  
CONDITION
The brooch and earrings are in great condition on both sides.

Product name: Roman Glass Beads, Silk Road Roman Glass, Rectangular Ancient Roman Glass Beads, Mineral Patina Glass Beads, 1 Bead Strand kbdesignsetc
Description:
ROMAN GLASS BEADS, a.k.a. Silk Road Beads, Rare Roman Glass Beads, Rectangular / Square Shaped Roman Glass Beads, Roman Glass Patina Beads, Ancient Roman Glass Bead Spacer Beads AR150
These rare and ancient Roman glass pieces are from around the 1st century or even earlier (i.e. B.C.), an unbelievably long time ago! 
Originally, these glass pieces were a part of a bowl, a goblet, a pitcher, some type of utilitarian vessel. They belong to the actual, every day existence and activities of Roman life. 
These vessels became buried over time.  The vast majority have, naturally, broken into pieces. 
A portion of these glass fragments have been made into beads. Every bead has individuality. The beads vary in color, patina, mineralization, dimensions, surface character...===  all adding up to the beads that we love, appreciate and covet.
Being in the ground for this long period of time has allowed these pieces to develop unique mineral patinas.
** THIS LISTING IS FOR ONE STRAND. 
** UNIQUE- Please note: the strands that we offer include Roman GLASS SPACER BEADS (we do not substitute; ALL the beads on these strands are made from genuine, remarkably old, unearthed glass).
The glass has sat for centuries, unfound, in the soil and ground. Therefore, much of the glass has collected mineral deposits. These mineral deposits have become the beautiful, opalescent patinas that we now see on these ancient glass beads. The patina the beads have acquired over the centuries is natural, highly variable and, at times, absolutely stunning!
** THIS LISTING IS FOR A SINGLE STRAND OF ROMAN GLASS FRAGMENT BEADS THAT ARE RECTANGULAR / SQUARE IN SHAPE. THE BEADS ARE BLUE, GREEN, AQUA, BROWN, YELLOW… SOME WITH PATINA, SOME ARE CLEAR. THEY ARE FREQUENTLY TEXTURED AND/OR WITH VARIATIONS IN SHAPE. EACH and EVERY BEAD IS UNIQUE.
The patina/mineralization of the beads can offer wonderful small flashes of color. You might see pink, green, red, blue...  These color flashes, in some of the patinas, will vary in different lighting; they resemble opals or labradorite etc...
** Approximately 14 - 21 ancient glass beads per strand which measure approximately 14 x 10 x 8 to 9 x 7 x 4 mm, PLUS the spacer beads that are approximately 3 x 5 mm rondelles. VARIATION in bead quantity does exist between the strands (however, the length of the beads on any selected strand remain, generally, equal to each other). Each bead is unique, no two pieces are exactly alike, therefore every strand is one of a kind.
The beads are cut from a variety of different ancient glass vessels. 
 The age of the glass ranges from 900 to 2700 years old.
*** YOUR BEAD STRAND/S WILL BE CHOSEN AT RANDOM FROM OUR INVENTORY***
We offer a variety of additional shaped ancient glass bead strands. Please ask.

Product name: Iittala Glasses Ultima Thule by Tapio Wirkkala, Finnish Designer, Mid-20th Century Classic - Set of Four Iittala Glasses in Original 60s Box
Description:
This set of four Iittala "Ultima Thule" glasses by the Finnish designer Tapio Wirkkala is in excellent original and unused condition. These classic Finnish glasses are mould blown, and were produced in 1968. You will see copies in top design shops that may cost more! These glasses are original and will hold their value, especially if you keep the box.
Ultima Thule is an evocation of the patterns nature gives to frozen water. Its tactile, textured surface overcomes the problems of machine-made glass and communicates a delicious sensation of cold by its frosted appearance.
These original collectible glasses can sell for up to 68 AUD each on Etsy or Ebay. This is a rare, intact set of four in the original foam box inside the original cardboard outer container, and in a vintage shop would cost much more than my price.
The height of each glass is 2.8 inches (7cm), and the diameter at the widest point is 2.8 inches (7cm).
Any excess postage costs will be refunded: PLEASE SEE MY POLICIES STATEMENT.

Product name: Vintage Carousel Horse Music Box - replica Looff c. 1911
Description:
This is a distinctive figurine of a carousel horse done in the style of Charles I.D. Looff circa 1911. The white horse is detailed in shades of blue, and the hand painting has been done with great attention to detail. 
The horse is secured by a brass pole to a wooden base on which a nameplate is affixed: Looff c. 1911
Looff was a famous carnival American master carver and builder of hand-carved carousels and amusement rides in the late 1800s and early 1900s. He became known for creating the Coney Island style of carousel carving. 
Unfortunately the music box function does not work. (Maybe a handy person will be able to repair it.)
On the bottom we have a label saying Impulse Giftware Made in Taiwan.
Size: Base is 5 1/4 inches long; 3 1/4 inches wide; and stands 1 1/2 inches tall. The horse figurine is approximately 4 7/8 inches long (from knee to tail); about 1 1/2 inches wide; and stands about 5 1/2 inches tall (excluding the base).
Condition: Very good vintage condition. You can see a few small nicks in the wooden base - please look carefully at the photos. And as mentioned, the music box doesn't play. But the figurine itself is in excellent condition -- no cracks, chips, repairs, or flaws. Give it a little gentle cleaning and polish up the brass pole and you will have a magnificent addition to your collection!

If you're a "wrongcolorphobe" like me :o) you prefer hanging pieces on your walls that blend with the undertones of the wall it's being hung on and its surrounds. That's why this is the perfect match for walls with gray/neutral  undertones where you don't want yellow/red undertones. I carefully select boards from wood species that will allow for this type of color blending but still showcases the natural grain and well earned character of each board.

If you decide to purchase one of my custom creations, we will collaborate on the design of your clock and you will receive a choice of mock-ups for your approval. 
As you will notice in the pictures, the clock has distinct knots, nail holes, and characteristics that are uniquely its own. Therefore, each clock will have its own special characteristics and no two clocks will be exactly alike. And that should be exactly why you're reading this description, you want authentic and you want unique! So ... you've come to the right place!

Product name: D20 Spindown Life Counter Die for MTG, Stainless Steel - 'Center Arc' Metal Balanced Dice
Description:
This is a twenty sided die (D20) that is intended to be used as a life counter for games such as Magic: the Gathering. The numbers on the die are arranged in a 'spindown' pattern, which makes it easier to find the next number up or down. The die is perfectly balanced so that it gives fair results when rolled.
This die is 3D printed in stainless steel, and is available in several different finishes. (See the last picture for examples of these options.) Because of the 3D printing process the surface of the die is slightly grainy. 
Because it is printed in steel it has a nice solid feel and weight to it. (This die weighs approximately 15 grams, whereas a regular plastic one weighs only about 6 grams.) The die is about 30 mm (1.2") high, when measured straight across between a each set of opposing faces. This is larger than a regular MTG spindown die, as you can see in the pictures. Picture 4 shows this die compared to my other design for a spindown d20, which is also available here on Etsy.
You will receive the die in its blank metal state. To give the die some more definition and make the numbers stand out more, you can easily darken or 'ink' the recessed parts. To do so take a small paintbrush and some thinned black acrylic paint (about one part water to one part black acrylic) and simply dab the thinned paint all over the die. Let it dry out (you can use a hairdryer to speed this up) and gently rub the painted die on a piece of cloth. This will remove the paint from the more exposed areas, and leave it behind in the folds and the background behind the numbers. If you missed a spot, or if you want a heavier effect just repeat these steps until you get it to look just the way you want.
Please be advised that, with the stainless steel material option, as a result of the production process, there can sometimes be some residual particles of polishing medium stuck in the details of the design. These bits of polishing medium (corn cob particles), which look like small grains of sand, can be easily removed using a pin, a toothpick or a small (wire) brush.

Product name: Premium Fire Rope Dart
Description:
Time to take your rope dart to the next level? The Fire Mecca Premium Rope Dart was designed with professionals in mind, and is perfect for anyone looking for a serious rope dart. 
We worked closely with several professional fire performers who specialized in rope dart to figure out exactly what they wanted from their tools. Arguably, the most important part of a rope dart is the rope, so that’s where we started. We tried numerous ropes, until we found the perfect blend of comfort, strength and durability in ¼” (6mm) braided hemp rope. At one end of the rope we have a hard rubber PX3 knob as a stopper, on the other a short length of stainless steel Twistlink chain with a swivel welded on each end to ensure the head never binds. 
With the body done, it was time to move on to the head. Most rope darts on the market utilize a large poi head, which works fine for most spinners, but our professionals wanted something more. The trick was creating something that meets Fire Mecca’s standards of aesthetics and durability while also meeting the needs of a serious rope dart user. The end result was an extra-large (5 inch) K1 1/4" Moonblaze head, built on a solid steel core with washers braided in to the head to improve flight without sacrificing the appearance. The end result is a rope dart head that’s a little on the heavy side, but flies like a dream. 
Rope Darts have many siblings and go by other names: chain dart, single headed meteor hammer, etc.
If the length you need is not an option please place length, up to 16 feet, in your order notes. Handmade to order locally in Tucson, AZ, USA.

Product name: Claddagh Ring (Women) -  A traditional Irish ring which represents love, loyalty, and friendship in 925 sterling silver for women
Description:
The Claddagh ring is a traditional Irish ring which represents love, loyalty, and friendship through the clasped hands which represent friendship, the heart representing love, and the crown representing loyalty.
The Claddagh ring belongs to a group of European rings called "fede rings" dating from Roman times, when the gesture of clasped hands was a symbol of pledging vows, and they were used as engagement/ wedding rings in medieval and Renaissance Europe.
Fede rings are cast in the form of two clasped hands, symbolising faith, trust, or “plighted troth”  The Claddagh ring is a variation on the fede ring.  Towards the end of the 20th century there was an explosion of interest in the Claddagh Ring, both as jewellery and as an icon of Irishness.  In more recent years it has been embellished with interlace designs and combined with other Celtic and Irish symbols, but this is a very recent phenomenon that corresponds with the worldwide expansion in popularity of the Claddagh ring as an emblem of Irish identity
Made in solid sterling silver our Claddagh ring is made to order to your finger size.  We make both male and female rings.  Please see

Product name: Love Letter to Biology 250 (Chella Courington) chapbook, micro fiction
Description:
Love Letter to Biology 250 is a chapbook of micro fictions by Chella Courington. This manuscript pinged our nerd-brains when we first read it, flirting with obscure tidbits from Biology lectures—those things we remember because they're strange—crafted into really tiny stories.
The cover is printed on Epson matte professional paper, each trimmed and bound by hand, finished with a hand-cut title flag typed (old school!) on kraft brown paper. The artwork, "Jelly Flyby," is watercolorink on paper (9 x 12 inches) by Jonathan Rountree, one of our in-house artists.
Excerpt from "Preferring a Clean Virgin:"
The male dark fishing spider climbs her Amazonian body, his legs under a third her size, her abdomen mountainous, fourteen times heavier than his, and he rocks her, side to side, his pedipalps engorged until the blood pushes too hard against arterial walls, curling him against her. Stuck to her, he’s consumed by her. The number and size of their offspring increased by his sacrifice.
About the Author
Chella Courington is Professor of Creative Writing at Santa Barbara City College. Her prose and poetry have appeared in numerous journals including The Los Angeles Review, lo-ball magazine, Gargoyle, The Tusculum Review, and Danse Macabre. In 2011 Courington published Paper Covers Rock, a flipbook of lined poetry, Indigo Press; Girls & Women, a chapbook of prose poetry, Burning River; and Talking Did Not Come Easily to Diana, an e-book of linked microfiction, Musa Publishing. Her work has been honored by Camroc Press Review, The Collagist, Qarrtsiluni, and Main Street Rag, and nominated for Best of the Net and Best New Poets Anthologies.
About the Cover Artist:
Jonathan Rountree (BFA Studio Art, Northern Kentucky University) is an aspiring world-traveler seeking to explore the intricacies of this realm armed with clay, camera, canvas, and paper.
About the Press:
Porkbelly Press creates chapbooks in handbound, small editions. Launched in 2014, PP seeks works with a strong sense of voice, place, and just a touch of fabulism, folklore, or magic. We make our home on the banks of the Ohio River, in a little town called Cincinnati, where pigs fly. // porkbellypress.wordpress.com
Editors: Nicci Mechler & Lauren Magee
Cover Artist: Nicci // damnredshoes.wordpress.com
(This listing is for one copy of the chap.)
What others are saying about Love Letter:
    “This collection is a work of freshness that is always surprising and never disappointing. Courington manages to do fascinating things with common images and she gives those images new life in a pleasing and sometimes disturbing oblique sort of light. Her terse, intense, and honest stories are presented in an earthy narrative voice in language full of longing and desire. These stories are both playful and provocative and can leave a reader almost breathless at times. Combined, the stories make up witty but also quite serious and worthwhile explorations.” —Pamelyn Casto, editor of Flash Fiction Flash Newsletter
    "Like a scientist in her laboratory, Chella Courington is careful and precise as she dissects the specimens before her. But Courington’s prose, like her eye, is enveloping, passionate yet also crystalline, hard and clean and clear, rewarding the discerning reader with these multifaceted gems." —Robin Lippincott, author of In the Meantime

Our popular standard birdcage veil is a modern classic.  Pair it with any of our fascinators or wear it alone for a classic vintage look.

These 5 pieces of glass are pre drilled, pre cut and smoothed with my glass grinder so they won't cut your fingers with sharp edges.  They are all ready to thread with fishing line and used as a sun catcher and/or wind chimes.
Cutting, grinding and drilling holes in glass isn't as easy as it sounds.  I have made all the mistakes, I have cut my self to pieces, I have shattered a lot of glass. I got all that out of my system and I finally figured it out.  So let me do the dirty work for you.  I have the supplies, I have the knowledge, some days I even have the skills and I have the mess already started.  What's a little more broken glass lying around?

I have tried to take some of the difficulty out of making something really unique and beautiful with glass.

WASHING YOUR KIGURUMI !
  * Turn your kigurumi inside out. This keeps the fabric from getting nappy.
  * Put it in the washing machine! Yep, our kigurumi are washing machine safe. 
  * Use any detergent you'd like. Using a fabric-softener is recommended and will hellp you to keep them soft.
  * Wash your kigurumi on "Cold" for its first cleaning. This helps the color set it. After the first wash feel free to use the "Warm" setting in case your kigurumi has got stubborn stains.
    You can use the "Normal" or "Permanent Press" cycle on your washing machine. If you're worried about your kigurumi, the "Gentle" cycle should also do the trick.
  * Never bleach your onesies. Using non-chlorine bleach is however safe. Chlorine bleach will damage the texture by destroying the fleece fibers. 
  * After the washing machine, you can either put your kigurumi in the dryer or hang it out to dry.
    If you hang it out to dry, be sure to keep it out of direct sunlight.
    If you use a dryer, we recommended using either the "Air Dry" or "Fluff Air" setting (with no hot air as it may cause shrinkage). 
 * To prevent wrinkles, take it out from the dryer and hang it as soon as it is done.
  * Never iron your fleece kigurumi. It will lay the pile texture flat hence the beauty will be destroyed. 
That's it!
WASHING: Machine Wash Cold, Non-Chlorine Bleach, Dry Flat, Do Not Iron, Do Not Dry Clean
